#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn48.53"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn48.53:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 48 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 48 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.53:0.2"
msgid "6. Sūkarakhatavagga "
msgstr "6. The Boar’s Cave "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn48.53:0.3"
msgid "53. Sekhasutta "
msgstr "53. A Trainee "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn48.53:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn48.53:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery. "

msgctxt "sn48.53:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

#. VAR: sekho → sekkho (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "sn48.53:1.4"
msgid "“atthi nu kho, bhikkhave, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma sekho bhikkhu sekhabhūmiyaṃ ṭhito ‘sekhosmī’ti pajāneyya, asekho bhikkhu asekhabhūmiyaṃ ṭhito ‘asekhosmī’ti pajāneyyā”ti? "
msgstr "“Mendicants, is there a way that a mendicant who is a trainee, standing at the level of a trainee, can understand that they are a trainee? And that a mendicant who is an adept, standing at the level of an adept, can understand that they are an adept?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn48.53:2.1"
msgid "“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe … "
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.53:2.2"
msgid "“atthi, bhikkhave, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma sekho bhikkhu sekhabhūmiyaṃ ṭhito ‘sekhosmī’ti pajāneyya, asekho bhikkhu asekhabhūmiyaṃ ṭhito ‘asekhosmī’ti pajāneyya. "
msgstr "“There is a way that a mendicant who is a trainee, standing at the level of a trainee, can understand that they are a trainee, and that a mendicant who is an adept, standing at the level of an adept, can understand that they are an adept. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn48.53:3.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma sekho bhikkhu sekhabhūmiyaṃ ṭhito ‘sekhosmī’ti pajānāti? "
msgstr "And what is a way that a mendicant who is a trainee can understand that they are a trainee? "

msgctxt "sn48.53:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, sekho bhikkhu ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti—"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant who is a trainee truly understands: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’. "

msgctxt "sn48.53:3.3"
msgid "ayampi kho, bhikkhave, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma sekho bhikkhu sekhabhūmiyaṃ ṭhito ‘sekhosmī’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "This is a way that a mendicant who is a trainee can understand that they are a trainee. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.230, sc4
msgctxt "sn48.53:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sekho bhikkhu iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant who is a trainee reflects: "

msgctxt "sn48.53:4.2"
msgid "‘atthi nu kho ito bahiddhā añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā yo evaṃ bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ tathaṃ dhammaṃ deseti yathā bhagavā’ti? "
msgstr "‘Is there any other ascetic or brahmin elsewhere whose teaching is as true, as real, as accurate as that of the Buddha?’ "

msgctxt "sn48.53:4.3"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "sn48.53:4.4"
msgid "‘natthi kho ito bahiddhā añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā yo evaṃ bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ tathaṃ dhammaṃ deseti yathā bhagavā’ti. "
msgstr "‘There is no other ascetic or brahmin elsewhere whose teaching is as true, as real, as accurate as that of the Buddha.’ "

msgctxt "sn48.53:4.5"
msgid "Ayampi kho, bhikkhave, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma sekho bhikkhu sekhabhūmiyaṃ ṭhito ‘sekhosmī’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "This too is a way that a mendicant who is a trainee can understand that they are a trainee. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn48.53:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sekho bhikkhu pañcindriyāni pajānāti—"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant who is a trainee understands the five faculties: "

msgctxt "sn48.53:5.2"
msgid "saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom. "

# NOTE: BB’s translation seems to me incoherent here.
msgctxt "sn48.53:5.3"
msgid "Yaṅgatikāni yaṃparamāni yaṃphalāni yaṃpariyosānāni. Na heva kho kāyena phusitvā viharati; "
msgstr "And although they don’t have direct meditative experience of their destination, apex, fruit, and culmination, "

msgctxt "sn48.53:5.4"
msgid "paññāya ca ativijjha passati. "
msgstr "they do see them with penetrating wisdom. "

msgctxt "sn48.53:5.5"
msgid "Ayampi kho, bhikkhave, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma sekho bhikkhu sekhabhūmiyaṃ ṭhito ‘sekhosmī’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "This too is a way that a mendicant who is a trainee can understand that they are a trainee. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn48.53:6.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma asekho bhikkhu asekhabhūmiyaṃ ṭhito ‘asekhosmī’ti pajānāti? "
msgstr "And what is the way that a mendicant who is an adept can understand that they are an adept? "

msgctxt "sn48.53:6.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, asekho bhikkhu pañcindriyāni pajānāti—"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant who is an adept understands the five faculties: "

msgctxt "sn48.53:6.3"
msgid "saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom. "

msgctxt "sn48.53:6.4"
msgid "Yaṅgatikāni yaṃparamāni yaṃphalāni yaṃpariyosānāni. Kāyena ca phusitvā viharati; "
msgstr "They have direct meditative experience of their destination, apex, fruit, and culmination, "

msgctxt "sn48.53:6.5"
msgid "paññāya ca ativijjha passati. "
msgstr "and they see them with penetrating wisdom. "

msgctxt "sn48.53:6.6"
msgid "Ayampi kho, bhikkhave, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma asekho bhikkhu asekhabhūmiyaṃ ṭhito ‘asekhosmī’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "This is a way that a mendicant who is an adept can understand that they are an adept. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn48.53:7.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asekho bhikkhu cha indriyāni pajānāti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant who is an adept understands the six faculties: "

msgctxt "sn48.53:7.2"
msgid "‘Cakkhundriyaṃ, sotindriyaṃ, ghānindriyaṃ, jivhindriyaṃ, kāyindriyaṃ, manindriyaṃ—"
msgstr "eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind. "

msgctxt "sn48.53:7.3"
msgid "imāni kho cha indriyāni sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhissanti, aññāni ca cha indriyāni na kuhiñci kismiñci uppajjissantī’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘These six faculties will totally and utterly cease without anything left over. And no other six faculties will arise anywhere anyhow.’ "

msgctxt "sn48.53:7.4"
msgid "Ayampi kho, bhikkhave, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma asekho bhikkhu asekhabhūmiyaṃ ṭhito ‘asekhosmī’ti pajānātī”ti. "
msgstr "This too is a way that a mendicant who is an adept can understand that they are an adept.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn48.53:7.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

